24/08/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Cypriots living abroad are gathering in Nicosia on Tuesday (August 24th) for a five-day conference on the reunification effort and other current issues.
The 23rd Conference of the Executive Councils of the World Federation for Overseas Cypriots (POMAK), the International Co-ordinating Committee "Justice for Cyprus" (PSEKA), and the 5th Annual Conference of the World Organisation for Young Overseas Cypriots (NEPOMAK) wraps up on Friday.
President Demetris Christofias and other senior officials will speak at the opening ceremony.
(CNA, Greek Reporter - 23/08/10)
